    value: 'The Black Jade (玄圭): A symbol of the Mandate of Heaven given by the legendary sage-king Yao to Yu the Great, representing the transmission of imperial authority.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'The Auspicious Dream of Zhou (協卜之夢): King Wen of Zhou dreamed of obtaining the support of Jiang Ziya (the Duke of Zhou), whose wisdom enabled Zhou to unify all under Heaven.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'Wihwa Island (威化島): The site of a crucial military maneuver where Taejo famously turned his army around to prevent a disastrous invasion, an event that altered the course of Korean history.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'The three Hans (三韓): Refers to the three ancient Korean kingdoms of Goguryeo, Baekje, and Silla, and poetically to the entirety of the Korean peninsula.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'Yi Saek (李穡): A renowned Confucian scholar and statesman who advised Taejo on matters of governance and diplomacy.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'Gojoseon (檀君朝鮮): The legendary first Korean kingdom, founded according to tradition in 2333 BCE, whose revival as a name symbolized continuity with ancient Korean civilization.'
